Case called at 1:38 pm
Defendant Roxanne M. Young in court with Attorney Matthew K Prior. ADA Monica J Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on Count #1 & #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court dismisses outright Count # 3, #4 & #5.

On each count, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 18 months, with conditions:
--AODA Assessment & Follow Through with any recommended treatment, per Agent
--Undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--Random urinalyses (1x per month for the first 6 months)
--Obtain/maintain employment and/or education program or combination of the two, per Agent
--No possession of any controlled substances without a valid prescription
--No contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes as approved by the agent
--To pay costs of $268, each count
--To pay $250 DNA Surcharge, each count
--To reimburse $50 drug testing fee
--To reimburse $70 in buy money
--To submitt DNA sample unpon demand

Court will not order any drivers license suspension in this case.
